54:39.170 --> 54:41.950
Have you slept? You look like crap.

54:41.960 --> 54:44.090
No primary matches for criminal record.

54:44.100 --> 54:48.190
Well, cross-check all state driver license
files and send this image to all local hospitals.

54:48.210 --> 54:51.350
Agent dunham, take a look at this.

54:56.230 --> 54:58.400
Oh, my god. This is him.

54:58.410 --> 55:00.210
He was a passenger on flight 627.

55:00.220 --> 55:01.770
- I don't-- I don't
understand. - Wait, wait, wait.

55:01.780 --> 55:03.180
He couldn't have been
at the storage place.

55:03.190 --> 55:06.400
- Charlie, I saw him there.
- hold on, guys.

55:06.410 --> 55:09.220
Morgan steig was passenger number 108.

55:09.230 --> 55:13.080
His emergency contact, richard steig.

55:13.090 --> 55:14.530
You're telling me he has a twin?

55:14.540 --> 55:17.890
Yeah, no home address, only
a history of employment.

55:17.900 --> 55:19.360
What?

55:19.370 --> 55:22.150
Richard steig's last employer.

55:28.110 --> 55:30.170
I was hoping to speak with william bell.

55:28.120 --> 55:32.720
<i>{\a6}MASSIVE DYNAMIC NEW YORK</i>

55:30.180 --> 55:32.760
I'm nina sharp, executive director.

55:32.770 --> 55:34.370
I only have a few minutes.

55:34.380 --> 55:38.740
our primary suspect is a former
employee of yours, richard steig,

55:38.750 --> 55:43.870
who may have used research from your company
to develop a self-eradicating airborne toxin.

55:43.880 --> 55:48.630
We don't know why or for whom, but it appears
he was willing to sacrifice his own brother.

55:48.640 --> 55:53.540
Whatever killed those people on that
plane got onboard through his insulin pen.

55:53.550 --> 55:56.660
So do you want to talk to me?

56:04.480 --> 56:06.460
Danielle...

56:06.470 --> 56:10.910
please assemble everything we have on
richard steig for agent dunham here.

56:13.040 --> 56:15.080
I remember richard steig.

56:15.090 --> 56:18.000
He worked in our weapons
systems research lab.

56:18.020 --> 56:22.740
He was caught three months ago trying to
leave the premises with classified information.

56:22.750 --> 56:24.610
He was terminated immediately.

56:24.620 --> 56:26.730
We referred his name to
the justice department.

56:26.740 --> 56:29.700
We have done our due
diligence, agent dunham.

56:29.710 --> 56:35.160
And if you choose to drag our company
and dr. Bell's name into this matter,

56:35.190 --> 56:37.270
you will be hearing from our attorneys.

56:37.280 --> 56:38.960
How long have you worked for dr. Bell?

56:38.970 --> 56:40.840
16 years.

56:40.850 --> 56:44.770
I owe massive dynamics my life,
and that is not an exaggeratioN.

56:44.780 --> 56:47.200
I s a runner most of my life.

56:47.210 --> 56:51.560
In the '97 boston marathon,
I felt strangely tired.

56:51.570 --> 56:57.090
One day at the office, dr. Bell noticed my
discomfort and insisted I go for a cat scan.

56:57.100 --> 56:59.410
Cancer.

57:00.950 --> 57:05.980
Spread so severely I had to
have my arm amputated that week.

57:05.990 --> 57:10.890
That first scanner that found my
cancer was built by this company.

57:10.900 --> 57:15.340
The robotic assist tools there were used in
my surgery, the drugs I took afterwards...

57:15.350 --> 57:19.120
were developed and manufactured
by massive dynamics.

57:19.130 --> 57:24.700
And my replacement limb was
designed by bell himself.

57:27.300 --> 57:31.390
Everything we have on richard steig.

57:31.930 --> 57:36.320
Do you believe that steig
may be part of the pattern?

57:36.330 --> 57:39.200
I'm sorry, part of the...

57:39.210 --> 57:41.260
part of the pattern?

57:41.270 --> 57:44.440
Oh, I assumed you had clearance.

57:45.650 --> 57:48.420
Well, I'm cleared to know whatever
you're cleared to know, ms. Sharp.

57:48.430 --> 57:51.210
Apparently not.

57:51.550 --> 57:55.000
But suffice to say that we've reached
a point where science and technology

57:55.010 --> 57:58.480
have advanced at such an
exponential rate for so long,

57:58.490 --> 58:03.320
it may be way beyond our ability
to regulate and control them.

58:04.740 --> 58:08.690
You should know what you're
getting into, agent dunham.

58:08.700 --> 58:11.750
I would say this to my own daughter.

58:11.760 --> 58:14.620
Be careful.

58:14.990 --> 58:18.220
And good luck.

58:23.630 --> 58:26.970
Keep the tree warm, sandy!
We're on our way to your house!

58:30.030 --> 58:32.090
And this is a show for children?

58:32.100 --> 58:34.160
Yeah, it's huge.

58:34.520 --> 58:38.670
Surprisingly profound for
a narrative about a sponge.

58:38.680 --> 58:40.060
Crazy house.

58:40.070 --> 58:41.980
I just landed at logan.
I'm on my way to you.

58:41.990 --> 58:43.920
I think we've located our suspect.

58:43.930 --> 58:45.910
Hold on a second. You found the guy?

58:45.920 --> 58:47.270
You found the guy from your dream.

58:47.280 --> 58:48.340
I'm picking you both up.

58:48.350 --> 58:49.840
I need your father
there to question him,

58:49.850 --> 58:52.070
get whatever information he needs
so he can make the cure for john.

58:52.080 --> 58:54.280
And I need you there too
in case your father's--

58:54.290 --> 58:56.550
say no more. We'll meet you out front.

58:59.780 --> 59:01.690
stay eyes on south side.

59:01.700 --> 59:03.790
red, stand by.

59:07.210 --> 59:09.550
rooftop, confirm your position.

59:10.540 --> 59:13.540
<i>{\a6}S*** BOSTON</i>

59:15.570 --> 59:17.010
Got one coming out.

59:18.050 --> 59:19.300
This way, ma'am.

59:30.410 --> 59:34.470
Clear! Clear! Clear!

59:36.240 --> 59:38.160
In the back!

01:00:10.420 --> 01:00:12.240
I'd like to... check
your blood pressure.

01:00:12.250 --> 01:00:15.500
Why don't you check your own blood
pressure? Mine's fine, thanks.

01:00:16.880 --> 01:00:20.520
Your skin tone suggests you might be
suffering from arterial hypertension.

01:00:20.530 --> 01:00:22.370
Don't tell me what I'm suffering from.

01:00:22.380 --> 01:00:25.850
And there are no visible
signs of hypertension.

01:00:28.830 --> 01:00:32.550
When this over, please
don't send me back.

01:00:32.560 --> 01:00:33.770
I don't want to go back.

01:00:33.780 --> 01:00:34.760
Look,
walter--

01:00:34.780 --> 01:00:40.280
this experience...You
woke me up again, and...

01:00:41.010 --> 01:00:42.590
you can't put me back to sleep.

01:00:42.600 --> 01:00:46.550
It was hardly my idea, any of it.

01:00:46.990 --> 01:00:51.520
Whatever punishment you think I deserve,

01:00:52.060 --> 01:00:55.880
I swear I have already endured it.

01:00:56.870 --> 01:01:01.340
17 years. Please...

01:01:01.890 --> 01:01:03.740
son.

01:01:13.670 --> 01:01:15.140
What?

01:01:15.150 --> 01:01:16.080
He's in the alley!

01:01:16.100 --> 01:01:17.150
Can I get out of the car?

01:01:17.160 --> 01:01:19.400
Stay right there, walter!

01:02:31.820 --> 01:02:34.590
We've got some questions for you.

01:02:36.110 --> 01:02:38.010
U.S.Code 1111.

01:02:38.020 --> 01:02:40.740
The murder of 147 passengers.

01:02:40.760 --> 01:02:43.380
U.S.Code 2332-A.

01:02:43.390 --> 01:02:46.060
Use of weapons of mass destruction.

01:02:46.070 --> 01:02:48.310
U.S.Code 2332-B.

01:02:48.330 --> 01:02:51.640
An act of terrorism
transcending national borders.

01:02:51.650 --> 01:02:53.590
U.S.Code 1132-A.

01:02:53.600 --> 01:02:56.570
Attempted murder of a federal agent.

01:02:56.580 --> 01:02:58.920
You want immunity.

01:02:58.930 --> 01:03:04.540
I want a detailed account of all the synthetic
chemicals you had in that storage facility.

01:03:04.560 --> 01:03:05.660
Write them down.

01:03:05.670 --> 01:03:09.370
And then we can talk about an agreement.

01:03:15.320 --> 01:03:19.780
I... have nothing... to say.

01:03:47.400 --> 01:03:50.100
Walter, stay here.

01:03:50.340 --> 01:04:06.000
Where
are you--

01:04:06.010 --> 01:04:07.940
the compound affecting agent scott.

01:04:07.950 --> 01:04:10.420
It's water soluble, right?

01:04:10.430 --> 01:04:14.570
We might not know what it
is, but we know what it does.

01:04:14.590 --> 01:04:19.800
So if I wanted to, I could extract the
contagious fluids from his body and...

01:04:19.810 --> 01:04:23.460
that would allow me to slip
it to you whenever I wanted to.

01:04:25.600 --> 01:04:27.860
In your food.

01:04:27.870 --> 01:04:29.660
A cup of coffee.

01:04:29.670 --> 01:04:31.800
The toilet.

01:04:31.810 --> 01:04:34.750
Nobody would ever know how it happened.

01:04:34.760 --> 01:04:36.490
The only problem is...

01:04:36.500 --> 01:04:40.890
the woman who was just in here,
that's her friend who's dying.

01:04:40.900 --> 01:04:43.930
So I just don't have that kind of time.

01:04:43.940 --> 01:04:45.400
No!

01:04:46.820 --> 01:04:47.830
Tell me the chemicals!

01:04:47.840 --> 01:04:50.210
Hey, stop, stop! You
can't! You can't do that.

01:04:50.220 --> 01:04:52.010
No, you can't do that.

01:04:52.020 --> 01:04:53.570
I want the names of the chemicals.

01:04:53.580 --> 01:04:55.770
I'm gonna count to one.

01:04:57.220 --> 01:04:58.780
One!

01:04:59.130 --> 01:05:02.030
The active toxin was a
magnesium based ethylene glycol.

01:05:02.040 --> 01:05:03.580
No, I understand that, but
you're not listening to me.

01:05:03.590 --> 01:05:06.170
Magnesium ethylene glycol
with an organophosphate trig--

01:05:06.180 --> 01:05:07.610
walter, just stop for a second.

01:05:07.620 --> 01:05:09.930
His blood won't be able to absorb
it before the side-effects kill him.

01:05:09.940 --> 01:05:10.830
So you're saying what?

01:05:10.840 --> 01:05:14.930
We synthesize a calcium
gluconate in a thiamine base?

01:05:14.940 --> 01:05:15.860
Yes, exactly.

01:05:15.870 --> 01:05:18.200
We can'T. We'd need more
of his blood. We have none.

01:05:18.210 --> 01:05:18.960
That's
not true--

01:05:18.970 --> 01:05:23.440
all agents are required to set up a
backup blood supply in case we're wounded.

01:05:23.450 --> 01:05:25.550
autologous transfusion.
That's brilliant.

01:05:25.560 --> 01:05:28.960
We can create the antidote and then just
dissolve it into scott's stored blood.

01:05:28.970 --> 01:05:32.100
If we transfuse him intravenously,
his body won't be overwhelmed.

01:05:32.110 --> 01:05:35.480
A+, boY. Well done. Let's begin.

01:05:58.670 --> 01:06:00.810
So I got the lab.

01:06:01.490 --> 01:06:04.080
Yeah, I know you did.

01:06:04.440 --> 01:06:06.810
Thanks.

01:06:09.550 --> 01:06:12.380
How's it goin' downstairs?

01:06:15.560 --> 01:06:20.920
bishop says it'll be awhile,
but that it's looking auspicious.

01:06:20.930 --> 01:06:23.730
That was his word.

01:06:24.230 --> 01:06:25.400
What?

01:06:25.410 --> 01:06:28.250
You've done some solid work here.

01:06:28.260 --> 01:06:32.930
Locating bishop. Getting him out.
Finding a way to get him to work with you.

01:06:33.290 --> 01:06:35.260
We're impressed.

01:06:35.270 --> 01:06:37.820
Who's "we"?

01:06:37.850 --> 01:06:42.140
What happened on that plane might be part of
something more dangerous than just simple terrorism.

01:06:42.150 --> 01:06:44.780
Simple terrorism?

01:06:46.680 --> 01:06:52.120
In the past nine months, there have been three dozen
authenticated incidents like the hamburg flight.

01:06:52.130 --> 01:06:56.040
John thompson, normal kid,
went missing back in '98.

01:06:56.050 --> 01:07:00.390
Reappeared last month halfway
around the world. Hadn't aged a day.

01:07:00.930 --> 01:07:05.230
In the past few months, 46 other children
who went missing that same year turn up.

01:07:05.240 --> 01:07:07.740
Same story.

01:07:07.760 --> 01:07:12.770
Local fisherman off the coast of sri lanka reports
a low-flying plane emitting a high-pitch frequency

01:07:12.780 --> 01:07:15.060
that blows out all their windows.

01:07:15.070 --> 01:07:17.040
An hour later, same spot,

01:07:17.050 --> 01:07:23.070
an 8.7 sub-surface earthquake creates
a tsunami that kills 83,000 people.

01:07:23.080 --> 01:07:25.280
- So why are you
telling me-- - this man.

01:07:25.290 --> 01:07:30.450
A patient in lisbon who woke up after
years in a coma began writing just numbers.

01:07:30.460 --> 01:07:35.620
They turn out to be exact real-time coordinates
of our carrier battle groups in the pacific.

01:07:35.640 --> 01:07:38.400
Intel that's classified
above top-secret.

01:07:38.410 --> 01:07:40.020
So how is that even possible?

01:07:40.040 --> 01:07:42.410
Come work for me, and I'll
get you the clearance--

01:07:42.420 --> 01:07:43.860
oh, stop.

01:07:43.870 --> 01:07:44.780
Dunham, there's more you need to hear.

01:07:44.800 --> 01:07:46.700
You must not have heard me. I said stop.

01:07:46.710 --> 01:07:48.430
They're calling these
events "the pattern."

01:07:48.450 --> 01:07:51.370
As if someone out there is experimenting,
only the whole world is their lab.

01:07:51.380 --> 01:07:52.690
You've seen it, now you know.

01:07:52.700 --> 01:07:54.350
I don't wanna know. I have a job.

01:07:54.360 --> 01:07:56.040
This is a more important job.

01:07:56.050 --> 01:07:59.010
Anything, anybody you
need, you can have.

01:07:59.020 --> 01:08:00.990
I like the job I've got.

01:08:01.000 --> 01:08:04.450
And the man I do it with. Which you
seem to have deduced on your own.

01:08:04.460 --> 01:08:06.320
Look around.

01:08:06.330 --> 01:08:08.310
You see all these people
going about their lives.

01:08:08.320 --> 01:08:12.210
No idea what's happening around
them, what they're in the middle of.

01:08:13.000 --> 01:08:16.090
I just wanna go back to before.

01:08:17.439 --> 01:08:22.050
Dunham. I don't think you can.

01:09:20.229 --> 01:09:21.479
He's up. He's awake.

01:09:21.490 --> 01:09:24.170
Olivia, olivia, he's
awake! He's conscious.

01:09:24.180 --> 01:09:25.830
John?

01:09:27.350 --> 01:09:32.170
John, can you hear me, baby? Baby?

01:09:32.880 --> 01:09:35.760
I had a dream about you.

01:10:02.720 --> 01:10:05.640
Uh, a change of clothes for agent scott.

01:10:06.180 --> 01:10:09.300
His vitals are surprisingly strong.

01:10:09.640 --> 01:10:12.540
So, um, how long does he have to stay?

01:10:12.570 --> 01:10:16.430
Until the melanocytes in his skin have
regenerated, but that shouldn't be more than a week.

01:10:17.090 --> 01:10:19.340
He owes you his life.

01:10:19.770 --> 01:10:22.200
We owe each other.

01:10:27.540 --> 01:10:30.360
What room is steig in?

01:10:31.960 --> 01:10:34.750
I told you everything I know. Didn't I?

01:10:34.760 --> 01:10:37.970
I gave you the names of all the
synthetics I used in the compound.

01:10:37.980 --> 01:10:40.970
Don't worry, our
immunity agreement holds.

01:10:41.000 --> 01:10:43.170
But there's still a whole lot
more we have to talk about.

01:10:43.180 --> 01:10:45.080
Like, why you killed your own brother?

01:10:45.090 --> 01:10:46.570
And who you're selling your work to?

01:10:46.580 --> 01:10:48.340
Who says I was selling it?

01:10:48.350 --> 01:10:51.710
I was threatened by a
guy from your office.

01:10:51.720 --> 01:10:54.190
You think I'm lying?

01:10:54.200 --> 01:10:56.530
I swear to god.

01:10:56.540 --> 01:11:00.380
I can prove it.

01:11:00.410 --> 01:11:03.680
- Where's the recording?
- I buried it.

01:11:46.500 --> 01:11:47.720
Who is this?

01:11:47.730 --> 01:11:49.230
we had an exchange agreement.

01:11:49.250 --> 01:11:51.400
hmm, there have been other bidders.

01:11:51.410 --> 01:11:54.390
Today, the airplane was a demonstration.

01:11:54.410 --> 01:11:56.280
you've drawn unwarranted attention.

01:11:56.290 --> 01:11:59.090
Something we can't afford
to be connected with.

01:11:59.110 --> 01:12:01.260
I'll make this simple. You're
not selling to anyone else.

01:12:01.270 --> 01:12:02.880
You do that, we will come after you.

01:12:02.890 --> 01:12:04.880
I will come after you.

01:12:04.890 --> 01:12:08.660
you're threatening me after seeing what
I'm willing to do to my own brother?

01:12:08.670 --> 01:12:11.920
well, let me assure you, we'd be
happy to treat you as family too.

01:12:11.930 --> 01:12:15.650
Well, let me assure you. We'd be
happy to treat you as family too.

01:12:28.860 --> 01:12:29.940
Special agent scott.

01:12:29.950 --> 01:12:34.920
Yes, sir, go right ahead.

01:12:58.460 --> 01:13:01.650
charlie, I need two agents posted
outside agent scott's room now.

01:13:01.660 --> 01:13:02.910
Check on steig.

01:13:02.920 --> 01:13:04.200
I'm on it.

01:13:04.210 --> 01:13:06.280
I'm five minutes away.

01:13:09.410 --> 01:13:12.370
We need this place locked down!

01:13:21.920 --> 01:13:28.260
This is dunham, agent I.D.52776 In pursuit
of blue suv heading south on fenway.

01:13:28.270 --> 01:13:30.430
Need immediate assist.

01:15:23.870 --> 01:15:27.090
Ask yourself why...

01:15:30.450 --> 01:15:37.900
why broyles sent you
to the storage facility.

01:15:40.300 --> 01:15:42.700
Why you?

01:15:42.710 --> 01:15:45.660
Why? I don't understand.

01:15:47.430 --> 01:15:50.640
Who are you working for?

01:15:51.620 --> 01:15:54.600
John, tell me.

01:15:54.610 --> 01:15:57.670
Tell me more, john.

01:16:51.350 --> 01:16:54.290
I knew him just as long as you did.

01:16:58.280 --> 01:17:00.580
I'm sorry.

01:17:02.990 --> 01:17:06.370
Job isn't what it was ten years ago.

01:17:07.690 --> 01:17:10.480
We're supposed to protect a world

01:17:10.490 --> 01:17:15.150
where one breath of the wrong air can
incinerate you from the inside out.

01:17:16.990 --> 01:17:19.890
I mean, how do we protect people

01:17:19.900 --> 01:17:25.100
when corporations have higher
security clearances than we do?

01:17:26.020 --> 01:17:30.230
When we're not fully briefed on half
the things that we're investigating?

01:17:30.240 --> 01:17:33.360
You know, when the truth...

01:17:36.710 --> 01:17:42.270
the truth is we're obsolete.

01:17:46.390 --> 01:17:49.040
Take me back to the lab.

01:18:07.620 --> 01:18:09.890
Can I talk to you please?

01:18:09.900 --> 01:18:11.810
Yeah. I'll be back in a second.

01:18:11.820 --> 01:18:16.370
Though I'm sure you're anxious to
get as far away from here as possible.

01:18:16.380 --> 01:18:19.950
To iraq or afghanistan or
countless other out of reach places,

01:18:19.960 --> 01:18:22.300
but I'm here to tell you that
your father needs to stay.

01:18:22.320 --> 01:18:25.900
Which means that you need to too.

01:18:25.910 --> 01:18:26.970
Are you okay?

01:18:26.980 --> 01:18:32.820
No, I-I-I-I know that you have countless
reasons as to why this is a non-starter for you.

01:18:32.830 --> 01:18:35.960
But, I mean, your father is a good man.

01:18:35.970 --> 01:18:38.050
He's not the monster you think he is.

01:18:38.060 --> 01:18:40.260
And you're good with him,
despite what you think.

01:18:40.270 --> 01:18:42.710
And you're the only
one who speaks walter.

01:18:42.730 --> 01:18:45.320
We take him back to st.
Claire's and it's all over.

01:18:45.330 --> 01:18:47.230
Where's john?

01:18:47.240 --> 01:18:49.490
I can talk to the agency and get
them to clear your gambling debts.

01:18:49.500 --> 01:18:54.330
I can take care of my own debts,
okay? What just happened? Where's john?

01:18:54.340 --> 01:18:56.710
